Leadership dominance tactics include: Coercive power tactics: Threats and force to persuade others. Punishment, force, and reward withholding are coercive power methods. Reward power tactics: These employ incentives to persuade others. Bonuses, promotions, and other rewards are reward power strategies. Legitimate power tactics: These employ legal authority to influence others. Orders, policies, and titles are valid power methods. Expert power techniques: These strategies employ expertise to persuade others. Information, problem-solving, and advice are expert power strategies. Referent power tactics: Using charm, likability, and trustworthiness to persuade people. Relationships, real interest, and leadership are referent power methods. Informational power tactics: Using information to persuade. Data, numbers, and proof are informational power strategies. 